cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper involves the use of computational models and machine learning techniques to extract temporal patterns from clinical time series data for predictive healthcare. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also involves the use of graph theory and network analysis to represent patient-clinician relations, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also involves the use of predictive models, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
